Name: Divine Solvent

Description: A silvery, silklike thread produced at the High Crucible of Al-Kimiya, used to enhance the properties of credendum attire. However, advances in crafting technology have rendered it obsolete.
Name: Divine Twine

Description: A dazzling substance produced at the High Crucible of Al-Kimiya, used to enhance the properties of credendum accessories. Why it smells slightly of rotten fish and amra is a mystery better left unsolved. However, advances in crafting technology have rendered it obsolete.
Name: Divine Shine

Description: While it is a surpassingly small means of storing knowledge, the information deposited on this relic of Allagan society was compressed with heretofore unseen efficiency. Such a wealth of knowledge would not come without a sacrifice to portability, however, and this tomestone is unfathomably heavy as a result. This particular variety is not as highly sought as it once was, and may no longer be exchanged for other wares.
Name: Hermetic Tomestone

Description: This hunk of meteorite contains deposits of a rare form of pyroxene. When subjected to an advanced extraction process, the achondrite produces mineral oil which can be used to manipulate the pathways of aetherial conductivity.
Name: Amplifying Achondrite

Name: Ballroom Etiquette - Wakeful Witchcraft

Description: An illustrated manual of how to effectively employ reference materials to support one's assertions in civilized debate. Use to learn the /reference emote.
Name: Ballroom Etiquette - Scrupulous Citations

Description:
Wear these lenses to feel and exude optimism.*
* Optimism may or may not be warranted. Please act according to actual conditions. Though these were once considered a fashion accessory, trends are ever changing, and style enthusiasts now classify them as facewear. Use to unlock rose-colored spectacles.
Name: Rose-colored Spectacles

Description: Designed in the likeness of a Far Eastern umbrella spirit, this parasol is certain to attract quizzical eyes (and slobbery tongues). Use to unlock a tsukumogami parasol.
Name: Tsukumogami Parasol

Description: A handy accessory to have when you need a large visual reminder that there is work to be done and schedules to keep. Use to acquire a tactful taskmaster umbrella.
Name: Tactful Taskmaster Umbrella

Description: A suit of chocobo armor designed to resemble Golbez.
Name: Voidcast Barding

Description: A suit of chocobo armor designed to resemble the felicitous furball.
Name: Felicitous Barding

Description:
Wants to work smarter, not harder.

Use item to acquire the puffin minion.
Name: Puffin

Description:
It's adorable now, but wait till it grows up.

Use item to acquire the mossasaurus minion.
Name: Mossasaurus

Description:

Use item to acquire the okuri chochin minion.

Use item to acquire the posher otter minion.
Name: Posher Otter

Description:

Use item to acquire the Rubellite Weapon minion.

This adorable critter will make you love every ape that you see, from chimpan-a to chimpan-z.

Use item to acquire the chimpanzee minion.
